item.title: A note on subvarieties of powers of OT-manifolds
item.description: arXiv:2408.08049v1 Announce Type: new Abstract: It is shown that the space of finite-to-finite holomorphic correspondences on an OT-manifold is discrete. When the OT-manifold has no proper infinite complex-analytic subsets, it then follows by known model-theoretic results that its cartesian powers have no interesting complex-analytic families of subvarieties. The methods of proof, which are similar to [Moosa, Moraru, and Toma ``An essentially saturated surface not of K\"ahler-type", {\em Bull. of the LMS}, 40(5):845--854, 2008], require studying finite unramified covers of OT-manifolds.
item.arxiv:journal_reference: Bull. Math. Soc. Sci. Math. Roumanie 58 (2015), 311-316
item.dc:creator: Rahim Moosa, Matei Toma

item.title: Certain Subclass of Harmonic Multivalent Functions Defined by New Linear Operator
item.description: arXiv:2408.08103v1 Announce Type: new Abstract: This current article aims to study a new subclass of meromorphic functions with positive coefficients by reconstructing a new operator in the punctured open disc. Also, some geometric properties are considered and investigated, such results as coefficient estimates, distortion and growth theorems, radius of starlikeness, convexity and close to convexity, extreme points, convex linear combinations, neighbourhoods, and integral transforms for a new class.
item.arxiv:journal_reference: Wasit Journal for Pure Sciences, 3(3),1-11, 30 September 2024
item.dc:creator: Ali H. Maran, Abdul Rahman S. Juma, Raheam A. Al-Saphory

item.title: On Picard's Theorem via Nevanlinna Theory
item.description: arXiv:2405.09659v5 Announce Type: replace Abstract: We consider the Picard's problem via Nevanlinna theory for complete K\"ahler manifolds with non-negative Ricci curvature. When the manifold is non-parabolic, which means that it carries a positive global Green function, we give a positive answer to the Picard's problem. That is, we confirm that every meromorphic function on such a (non-compact) manifold reduces to a constant if it omits three distinct values.
item.dc:creator: Xianjing Dong

item.title: Convergence Speed for Fekete Points on Uniformly Polynomially Cuspidal Sets
item.description: arXiv:2408.03053v2 Announce Type: replace Abstract: We obtain the convergence speed for Fekete points on uniformly polynomially cuspidal compact sets introduced by Pawlucki and Ple\'sniak. This is done by showing that these sets are $(\mathscr{C}^{\alpha}, \mathscr{C}^{\alpha'})$-regular in the sense of Dinh, Ma and Nguyen.
item.dc:creator: Hyunsoo Ahn, Ngoc Cuong Nguyen

item.title: Convergence from the discrete to the continuous non-linear Fourier transform
item.description: arXiv:2311.03511v2 Announce Type: replace-cross Abstract: In this note, we study the convergence from the discrete to the continuous non-linear Fourier transform. Relations between spectral problems and questions in complex function theory provide a new approach to the study of scattering problems and the non-linear Fourier transform \cite{Scatter}. In particular, the non-linear Fourier transform can be viewed from the perspective of spectral problems for differential operators. Results in \cite{MP, PZ} can be seen as results for the non-linear Fourier transform. These results are similar to some convergence problems for the discrete non-linear Fourier transform considered in \cite{T} and \cite{TT}.
item.dc:creator: Ashley R. Zhang

item.title: On strong growth conditions for weighted spaces of entire functions
item.description: arXiv:2401.14330v2 Announce Type: replace-cross Abstract: We characterize the inclusion relations between weighted classes of entire functions with rapid decreasing growth and study strong growth comparison relations between given weights. In our considerations first we focus on weights defined in terms of the so-called associated weight function where the weight(system) is based on a given sequence. Then the abstract weight function case is reduced to the weight sequence setting by using the so-called associated weight sequence. Finally, we compare weighted entire function spaces defined in terms of so-called dilatation-type and exponential-type weight systems.
item.dc:creator: Gerhard Schindl
